  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Integrated COVID-19 Response Programme for the Rohingya and Surrounding Host Communities_DAM</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">The main purpose of this project is to provide home-based health care services to COVID-19 confirmed cases and to create awareness among the Rohingya community people to lessen the spread of COVID-19 in the targeted area.  In Health, home-based health care services have been designed to prioritize People with Disability, Children, Elderly people and pregnant and lactating women. Health service providers (Doctors &amp; Nurses), Community Health Workers (CHWs) &amp; Volunteers will be provided with capacity building training on COVID-19 Infection, Prevention &amp; Control (IPC) mechanism as well as home-based care. Training will be also provided to faith based religious leaders (Imam) on misbelief and rumours related to COVID-19. Thus, the Imam, considered a trusted source of information, will play vital role in tackling rumours by disseminating approved messaging on Covid-19. CHW and community volunteers will visit households in the targeted areas, identify and referring suspected cases of COVID-19 to laboratory/booth for testing.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Increased access to home-based health care services for the confirmed COVID-19 cases
 Increased knowledge of health facilities staff and CHW in home-based Covid 19 care
Reduced misbeliefs and spread of rumours about Covid 19 in the targeted area
Improved hygiene practices to prevent COVID-19 spread in Rohingya Refugee Camp</narrative>
  </description>
